To achieve a better understanding of the use of gas for heating and other possible uses such as domestic hot water production, performance lines for every building are generated using the degree-days theory [23]. These performance lines are useful for measuring savings derived from energy conservation retrofits and to identify and correct operational and maintenance problems [24]. The estimated gas consumption for a heating period can be calculated as (Eq. 1):1F=24·HLC·HDDη+B,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
