As the billing periods for gas are not always regular in the number of days between gas readings, for each period, the gas consumption per day has been correlated with the HDD per day, by dividing both the gas readings and the HDD by the exact number of days of that particular billing period [25]. Thus, for each building, the slope (m) and the intercept (b) of a regression line (Eq. 3) is determined:3Fn·A=m·HDDn+b,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
