Daily aggregated electricity consumption values for the 2 years are plotted versus average daily exterior temperature values to determine the climatic dependence of electricity consumption. For the 18 buildings with natural gas heating, a cooling 4 parameters (4P) model will be applied. This model has the following mathematical formulation, [24, 27] (Eq. 5):5E=C+B1T-Tcb++B2Tcb-T+,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
